# Deploy on request (localhost 3040 → GitHub → Vercel)

This project is **patient-conversion-tool** (dev server: `localhost:3040`).

When the user says **"commit and push to github"** (or clearly equivalent wording):

1. Work in `/Patient-Conversion-Tool` (not Acuity or sibling repos unless they specify otherwise).
2. Run `git status`, `git diff`, and `git log -1` to review changes.
3. Stage relevant files only — never commit secrets (`.env`, tokens).
4. Write a concise commit message focused on **why**.
5. `git commit` then `git push origin main`.
6. Confirm the commit hash and remind them Vercel will deploy from GitHub automatically.

**Do not** commit or push unless the user gives this explicit instruction.
